  "body": "Besu rejected a block on mainnet and the top-level logs didn't make that clear. When we reject a block, we should surface the lower-level logs so that users running Besu with the default logging options see the block has been rejected. \n\nContext on the specific rejected block was shared in the [AllCoreDevs discord](https://discordapp.com/channels/595666850260713488/745077610685661265/761132890615709716). \n\nNote from @shemnon: \n> Besu is reporting it via `debug_getBadBlocks`, however our validation errors currently log below INFO (at DEBUG and TRACE)\n",
